bio:
Landscapes to experience, stories to tell.
Bainbridge Island, Washington

social_posts.post_text: Floating above the Northern California coast.
One from the winter archives ❄️
Coastal explorations with @laurenjeanmusic
Fall Kaleidoscope in the Cascades
Throwback to summer fire lookouts with @kylekotajarvi . Can’t wait until these trails melt off again.
A morning walk around Cape Kiwanda.
Winter setting in in the Olympics.
The beginnings of summer in Oregon.
Rays in the Redwoods. Always in the pursuit of the lighting conditions that makes these happen, they don’t last long, but when things line up it’s well worth the effort.
Some local neighbors. It still blows my mind that eagles are a common site souring through the skies here in the PNW.
An ode to the Olympics, my “home” National Park. Only an hours drive away but so much still left to explore.
Tranquil moments on the Washington coast.
One of the most unique places I ever experienced in California.
Some golden light in the Cascades last fall. Looking forward to summer in mountains.
High surf on the Washington coast.
Morning stillness on Two Medicine Lake. The East side of Glacier is my new favorite place to catch a sunrise.
The many textures of Death Valley National Park. This park is endless, so much more to explore.

Wildflower season in the Grand Tetons. Every angle in the Teton Valley provides a new perspective on the Teton range rising dramatically to the sky. 

 #optoutside #getoutside #outdoors #wyoming #lifeofadventure #stayandwander #exploremore #grandtetons #nationalparks
Fleeting summer light on one of Washington’s many fire lookouts. One of many I need to visit this summer…
Solo mountain peak missions, testing out the telephoto lens on the Mavic 3 pro. Stoked on the new angles and compression that camera can achieve.
When you hike to a lake for sunrise in the Tetons and walk straight into a real life painting.
Layers of the Olympics
This spot was my first introduction to Washington’s alpine lakes and I was hooked.
Summer nights at the base of Mt. Rainier.
Floating high above Owens Valley 🦅
Morning light in the Mountains > everything
Taking a walk across Rainier’s best infinity pool.
Some my favorite moments from adventures in the Southwest. Still one my favorite landscapes to photograph.
Low clouds and perfect light made for some dreamy drone shots a few weeks back in the Mt. Baker area. Can you spot one Washington’s many fire lookouts?
A summer night on the Washington Coast 🌊

Exploring one of the quietest places in the US. The Olympic Peninsula rain forests are not only the wettest places in the US (receiving over 100 inches of rain per year) but also contain one of the quietest places in the US.
Beginning of September means it’s almost Larch season here in WA. Looking forward to cooler days and less crowds for some fall hikes.
Exploring the land of granite and tarns high in the Washington backcountry.
A perfect misty morning on the Oregon Coast.
A summer morning at my new favorite lookout in the North Cascades.

Got to spend a night at one of North Cascades National Park’s highest backcountry camps at 7,400’. At the base of one of the park’s many glaciers, it truly was an alpine dream of endless peaks, glacial streams, and some curious mountain goats.
Some of my favorite shots from exploring around Rainier this summer. Still blows my mind that this big ol’ volcano is right in my backyard.
Some blue hour magic from a recent night in the backcountry.
I think this was the best sunset and bluest lake I captured all summer, and all in the same scene.
Take a walk around a fire lookout perched in the North Cascades with some of the best views imaginable. An endless sea of peaks as far as the eye can see. Need to get back up for an overnight visit.

This was the first time in a while that conditions really lined up for me to shoot the night sky in Washington (cloud cover, moon, season, etc) and luckily I was at one of the best backcountry camps in the North Cascades. These shots also use Lightroom’s Denoise AI, which is impressive considering these are single shots taken at 8000 ISO.
A stunner of a morning at Mt Baker. The sheer size of the glaciers that ring Baker’s peak always blows my mind.
Peak fall color in the Enchantments. This was my first time in this area and the sheer number and size of the larches blew me away. I guess you could say I was “enchanted” 😀
Some of my favorite shots from a combined 28 miles of hiking last week to catch some WA alpine fall color. Couldn’t have asked for better conditions.
Walking through a forest of gold. Fall in Washington was incredible this year, now heading South to catch some more of Fall in California.
Some sunrise and sunset shots from a night in the North Cascades. Definitely some of the best light I’ve ever captured.
Exploring one of my favorite spots in California with @laurenjeanmusic & @alexandr_ford
Some short moments from backpacking this summer in the Washington wilderness. Already looking forward to next season.
I recently made it back to Yosemite Valley, one of my favorite places to photograph. The valley really does provide some of the best light for landscapes, no matter the season.
Walking among giants with @laurenjeanmusic
Some of my favorite captures from the Washington Coast.
Road side attractions in California.
A morning cruise with @alexandr_ford . This bend in Glacier Point Road has to be one of the most scenic in all of California, with a perfect reveal of Half Dome coming around the corner.

Ringing in 2024 with my top 10 favorite images I captured in 2023. Took some time off of social media for the holidays, but looking forward to another year of exploring and capturing images in the outdoors.
Small moments from the holidays spent on the Northern California coast with family and friends.
A scene from a summer evening somewhere on a backroad in Montana. Pulling over to catch the last light of the day I realized there wasn’t a soul in sight - and I couldn’t have been happier.
Some winter scenes to go with the frigid 17 degrees we are experiencing here in Washington. ❄️

Sometimes in the pursuit of grand landscapes here in WA I forget just how lucky I am to be surrounded by the everyday beauty of life on the Puget Sound. Winter weather has been keeping me more local lately so I have been focusing on taking in the sites right in my own backyard.
When your friend gets a cool new Porsche you definitely have to take it for a rip in the Redwoods.
Some scenes from a classic California road trip.
A little slice of summer in the middle of winter.

Landscapes to experience, stories to tell.
Bainbridge Island, Washington
